description:
The Seventh-day Adventist church was mainly founded by young people, with the average age of the pioneers being well below 35. However, the time would come, as the church grew, dedicated work for the Adventist youth would need to be started. From humble beginnings in rural Michigan, two young men, Henry Fenner and Luther Warren would birth an idea that would grow to be the worldwide ministry it is today.

To find out more about our Adventist Youth Ministries visit our website to read our extended article. 
https://lineagejourney.com/read/the-birth-of-adventist-youth-ministries
